question_text: Mary told her friend Sharice that she had a rug to sell. Sharice asked if the rug would fit perfectly, wall to wall, in her bedroom. Mary went home and measured the rug. answer: - They could make sure both measurements include any moldings or baseboards around the edges of Sharice's bedroom walls.
